&lt;section class=&quot;Job_column1__SMcVh&quot;&gt;
&lt;h2 class=&quot;h6 text-red uppercase&quot;&gt;AT A GLANCE&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;RVO Health seeks a full-time Nurse Practitioner or Physician Assistant to join our interdisciplinary medical weight loss team. As a provider, you will diagnose, treat, and manage obesity as a chronic disease and its related comorbidities. This whole-person, programmatic primary care model transforms virtual healthcare nationwide by supporting each patient with care navigators, case managers, dietitians, and medical providers. This fully remote, full-time role offers a Monday–Friday schedule with no weekends or holidays.&lt;strong data-stringify-type=&quot;bold&quot;&gt;&lt;em data-stringify-type=&quot;italic&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We’re excited to begin accepting applications! Please note that we won’t be reaching out for a few months. Thank you for your patience—we’ll be in touch soon! &amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/section&gt;
&lt;section class=&quot;Job_column2__EY2DH&quot;&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will deliver virtual primary care focused on obesity management through synchronous (real-time) virtual telemedicine. All duties must comply with state and federal laws and adhere to evidence-based medical standards. This role offers the flexibility to telecommute from anywhere in the U.S. while tackling important healthcare challenges.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Primary Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver comprehensive virtual medical weight loss care including patient evaluations, diagnoses, treatment planning, chronic condition management and follow-up care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely with a multidisciplinary team including dietitians, care navigators, case managers, behavioral health professionals and external specialists to ensure coordinated whole person care.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Order and interpret diagnostic tests, prescribe appropriate medications and evidence-based treatment regimens, and adjust care plans as clinically indicated.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engage patients in shared decision-making, clearly explaining treatment options, risk and benefits while promoting adherence to prescribed regimens and follow-up care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver culturally responsive, patient-centered counseling that fosters sustainable lifestyle changes and ensures a safe, respectful space for patients to share challenges and successes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate effectively and compassionately via synchronous telemedicine visits and asynchronous messaging, addressing patient concerns promptly and thoroughly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in regular clinical team meetings and care conferences, contributing to case discussions, continuous learning and practice involvement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate care and exchange relevant patient information with local healthcare providers/organizations in compliance with HIPAA and state telehealth regulations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain thorough and timely documentation in the EHR, ensuring clear, compliant and up-to-date pt records.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support operational excellence by performing necessary administrative tasks and adhering to collaborative practice agreements and state specific telehealth laws.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What We’re Looking For&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Obesity medicine certification or training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous telemedicine experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Multi-state licensure (compact or multiple states) - preferred 10+&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with value-based or outcomes-oriented care models.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Team-oriented and mission aligned.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent presentation skills for both clinical and non-clinical audiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;

&lt;section class=&quot;Job_column1__SMcVh&quot;&gt;
&lt;h2 class=&quot;h6 text-red uppercase&quot;&gt;AT A GLANCE&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;RVO Health Media is dedicated to giving people a better path to health and wellbeing. We own and operate the largest health and wellbeing platform in the U.S., reaching more than &lt;strong&gt;70 million people each month&lt;/strong&gt; as they seek trusted health information, find care, compare prices, discover product discounts, save money, and take meaningful action in their health journeys. Our flagship sites include &lt;em&gt;Healthline and Healthgrades.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fullspan Health&lt;/strong&gt;, an offering from RVO Health, is helping life sciences companies engage patients across the entire healthcare journey. Offering end-to-end capabilities, from patient finding and engagement to pharmacy and care services and medication adherence, Fullspan Health combines trusted content, innovative digital tools, and data-driven insights to deliver a seamless, patient-centric experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Sales Team drives digital advertising revenue across the organization. We collaborate closely with marketing, analytics, media, and product teams to deliver high-performing advertising solutions that align with client needs. We focus on building strong, consultative relationships with clients and agencies while identifying strategic opportunities for growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role focuses on digital advertising media sales across the &lt;strong&gt;pharmaceutical, consumer health, cpg, insurance, etc &lt;/strong&gt;categories&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;. As an &lt;strong&gt;Associate Director, Digital Advertising Sales &lt;/strong&gt;you will be focused on new business development. Responsibilities include supporting revenue generation, developing and fostering client relationships, contributing to strategic solutions, and playing a key role in elevating RVO Health Media’s visibility within the marketplace. This is an ideal role for someone with strong prospecting skills, emerging sales experience who is ready to take on greater ownership, engage directly with clients, and advance toward a full sales leadership path.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a motivated, insights-driven seller with a passion for healthcare and digital media. Candidates with experience at media agencies, in account management, or in early-stage sales roles will be well positioned for success.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Where You&#39;ll Be&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;Note on Location:&lt;/span&gt; While this is a remote-first position, to ensure alignment with our core regional operations and team syncs, we are specifically looking for candidates currently residing in the &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;Northeast corridor (NY, NJ, CT, or the Greater Philadelphia area)&lt;/span&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/section&gt;
&lt;section class=&quot;Job_column2__EY2DH&quot;&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support revenue growth by managing and nurturing existing client partnerships.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify new opportunities and assist in developing strategic, insight-driven media solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in client and agency presentations, both virtually and in person.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help plan and execute client-facing events, meetings, and proactive outreach.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with media strategy and marketing teams to build integrated solutions that meet client goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain Salesforce pipeline updates and contribute to accurate forecasting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop familiarity with pharmaceutical market dynamics, client needs, and category nuances.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and secure new business opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What We’re Looking For&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;BA/BS degree or equivalent experie

&lt;section class=&quot;Job_column1__SMcVh&quot;&gt;
&lt;h2 class=&quot;h6 text-red uppercase&quot;&gt;AT A GLANCE&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are at a tipping point in global metabolic health. At RVO Health, we’re not just selling a&amp;nbsp;platform; we’re redefining how millions of people manage weight health through clinical rigor&amp;nbsp;and digital innovation. We are looking for a &lt;strong&gt;market-maker&lt;/strong&gt; and a &lt;strong&gt;relentless hunter&lt;/strong&gt; to serve as&amp;nbsp;the face of RVO Health’s weight care expansion. You will open doors that others find locked,&amp;nbsp;leverage your deep industry network to ignite rapid revenue growth and establish RVO Health&amp;nbsp;as the undeniable leader in B2B weight care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/section&gt;
&lt;section class=&quot;Job_column2__EY2DH&quot;&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sales Strategy and Execution&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive revenue through strategic partnerships with benefits brokers &amp;amp; consultants&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Architect and lead a full-cycle enterprise sales strategy – from initial prospecting and pipeline building to complex deal negotiations– with a focus on “jumbo” accounts&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Think like a CFO, developing and presenting the business case and ROI story for our offerings&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and maintain reporting on pipeline status, execution, and sales performance metrics using the best emerging AI tools&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Relationship Management&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cultivate and influence executive-level relationships, serving as a trusted advisor, while optimizing sales potential by understanding the client’s clinical and operational challenges&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage existing industry contacts and relationships to establish an early base of interest while soliciting product feedback&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaboration&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and leverage clinical and product cross functional teams throughout the sales process&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Energize and influence internal stakeholders, anchoring on your depth of market intelligence and empathy for our patient experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Market Analysis&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exploit market opportunities, looking around corners to identify emerging industry trends&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track competitor offerings, regulatory changes, and customer needs to inform business development priorities and strategic decision-making&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What We’re Looking For&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of proven success in business development or partnership management within the digital health, payer, or health system sectors&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven success exceeding quotas and closing $1M+ enterprise deals by aggressively hunting and closing net-new logos.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A &#39;player-coach&#39; mentality—someone who is just as comfortable building the playbook as they are running the play in the field&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Subject matter expertise in digital health enterprise solutions, preferably with metabolic health, pharmacotherapy interventions for weight health&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Executive presence with the ability to captivate C-level audiences and serve as a persuasive industry evangelist&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to thrive in a fast-paced, dynamic environment while effectively managing multiple projects and competing priorities&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willingness to travel 50%+ to engage stakeholders and represent RVO Health at key industry events&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pursuant to various state

&lt;section class=&quot;Job_column1__SMcVh&quot;&gt;
&lt;h2 class=&quot;h6 text-red uppercase&quot;&gt;At A Glance&lt;/h2&gt;
We are currently seeking a Human Resources Manager to join our growing Human Capital team at RVO Health. The HR Manager will provide support in a variety of critical HR functions such as benefits + open enrollment, payroll integration, leaves, HRIS data management, total rewards, etc. 
&lt;h2&gt;Where You&#39;ll Be&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To prioritize togetherness, culture, and accountability, RVO Health operates on an in-office work schedule. We expect employees to work from our South Charlotte&amp;nbsp;office Tuesday, Wednesday and Thursday each week. You are welcome to work remotely Mondays and Fridays if you wish.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;101 Red Ventures Dr Fort Mill, SC 29707&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/section&gt;
&lt;section class=&quot;Job_column2__EY2DH&quot;&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and manage HR Ops implementations, special projects, and programs.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage HRIS systems and programs (ADP WFN).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform routine tasks required to administer and execute human resource programs including but not limited to leaves; workers compensation; total compensation, benefits, and leave; disciplinary matters; disputes and investigations; productivity, recognition, and morale; occupational health and safety; and training and development.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage offboarding and onboarding employees including termination procedures, cross team coordination and benefit termination paperwork.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and develop standard operating procedures, workflows, communications, newsletter etc.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Audit systems, employment practices and propose recommendations for improvements.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare confidential documentation to support compliance, investigations or other.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain compliance with federal, state, and local employment laws and regulations, and recommended best practices; review policies and practices to maintain compliance.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with HR Business Partners and Human Capital team to develop or revise processes to maximize performance and deliver best-in-class services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Promote, articulate, and present HR operations, HR Ops tools, leveraging potentially different communication skills/mediums targeting different stakeholders (HR, Finance, employees, managers, IT).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain positive relationships internally and externally and collaborate with all support business partners to reach Company goals by executing HR operations.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct report writing, maintaining, gathering/scrutinizing, organizing, and analyzing data from multiple sources (Workday, ADP, and other HR tools) prepare graphs, reports, and presentations.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as first point of contact for employees on personal information changes, benefit updates, leaves, policy, procedures, and many other HR related questions.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What We’re Looking For&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in Human Resources, Business Administration, or a related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years of progressive work experience in Human Resources.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years’ experience in a Generalist role directly supporting employees in exempt-level roles.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working in ADP Workforce Now. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge and experience administering LOAs.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable in a fast-paced and often-changing environment.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must have the ability to multi-task and prioritize quickly.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
