&lt;h2&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own day-to-day workforce management operations for designated business units, serving as the primary point of contact for staffing and demand management needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and update staffing and demand models to reflect current headcount, enrollment trends, and capacity requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support short- and long-term forecasting by gathering and organizing data from internal systems and business stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and report on key workforce metrics including staffing levels, utilization, and demand variances, flagging risks and anomalies to senior team members.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform recurring workforce analyses and contribute to ad hoc requests in support of Talent programs, operational reviews, and business initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain standard workforce reports and dashboards to support visibility into business unit performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in the transition and documentation of workforce management processes currently managed by external partners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with program operations, HRBPs, and Talent teams to ensure workforce data and models reflect real-time business conditions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the broader Workforce Planning team with data gathering, reporting, and project execution as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
